redcap:Alerts.alert_message:
Thank you, [name_first]. Each day we will SMS this phone with instructions on how to take your measurements.

Please complete your first observations by clicking here [survey-url:ob_0]
Hello [name_first]. Thank you for registering with the RMH COVID-19 Home Monitoring Program. Please show this message to the hospital staffmember who registered you.

Hello [name_first]. You have reached the end of your monitoring period with the Royal Melbourne Hospital. If you have any concerns about your virus status you can contact the RMH COVID Home Monitoring Team on 0491570156

redcap:Alerts.email_subject: You've reached the end of your observation period
redcap:Alerts.alert_message:
Hello [name_first],

It is now enough time since your symptoms began that your home monitoring period with the Royal Melbourne Hospital can end.

If you have any concerns about your virus status you can contact the RMH COVID-19 Home Monitoring Program on 0491570156

[calc_name_display] (UR [ur]), has reached the end of [mon_period_days] days of their monitoring window and is due to be discharged.

Click this link to to discharge the patient:
[form-url:discharge]

Hello [name_first]. You're now well into the period between your first symptoms and when we expect the virus to run it's course.

Remember if your situation degrades for any reason you should get in contact with us to reassess you. That might include:

  - you begin running a fever

  - you have trouble breathing

  - your cough worsens

  - you find yourself more out of breath than usual


If you have any concerns about your virus status you can contact the RMH COVID-19 Home Monitoring Program on 0491570156
